cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is about detecting malicious scripts in JavaScript files using static analysis and neural networks. The primary focus is on cybersecurity (cs.CR), but the use of neural networks for classification suggests that it could also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of static analysis for processing large amounts of data, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of byte sequences suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) could also be a relevant sub-category.
